==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timothy grass
<hw>Tim"o*thy grass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[From
<ets>Timothy</ets> Hanson, who carried the seed from New England to
Maryland about 1720.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of grass
(<spn>Phleum pratense</spn>) with long cylindrical spikes; -- called
also <altname>herd's grass</altname>, in England, <altname>cat's-tail
grass</altname>, and <altname>meadow cat's-tail grass</altname>. It is
much prized for fodder. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timothy</ent>⟦br⟧
